                            <comment id="12760322" author="millerjam" created="Mon, 28 Sep 2009 19:13:44 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is a patch and unit test for single value field that counts missing for facets.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure about multivalue fields, but I could try if someone points me in the right direction.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12760574" author="gsingers" created="Tue, 29 Sep 2009 13:24:50 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Multivalued stuff is implemented in UninvertedField.java&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12760594" author="gsingers" created="Tue, 29 Sep 2009 13:53:32 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch that tests for missing in multivalued, and thus fails.  Fix still needs to be implemented.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12761573" author="gsingers" created="Fri, 2 Oct 2009 14:32:32 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I committed the fix for the single value case.  Committed revision 821014.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t have good bearings yet on fixing the multivalued case.  I am going to open up a new issue and move that to 1.5, unless someone wants to take it up.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12762459" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Tue, 6 Oct 2009 01:08:11 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Found it... in UnInvertedField.getStats(), the FieldType was being overwritten by the type of the facet fields.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12775893" author="gsingers" created="Tue, 10 Nov 2009 15:52:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for Solr 1.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
